pageContext.claim: “You remember that Barack Obama said that there is no way it [Brexit] is going to happen, and the U.K. will get to the back of the line if it ever does, right?”
pageContext.analysis: Obama never said Brexit would not happen. He did encourage the United Kingdom to stay in the European Union, saying Britain would be "at the back of the queue" for a U.S. trade deal if Brexit was approved.
